I"Å<p>Unapologetics: a play on the word <em>unapologetic</em>, meaning put forth without qualification, and the word <em>apologetics</em>, based on the Greek <em>apologia</em>, meaning a systematic argumentative discourse in defense of an idea.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p>I affirm, not as a means of opinion, that Christ is supreme, in all things, at all times, in all endeavors, and in all places, and that mankind is in open rebellion to this supremacy.</p>
